== Mupen64Plus ==

[[File:Mupen64plus_screenshot1.png|thumb|right|150px|Mupen64Plus [https://code.google.com/p/mupen64plus/wiki/Screenshots more...]]]

Mupen64Plus is a cross-platform plugin-based fork of the famous Mupen64 Nintendo 64 emulator. Included are four MIPS R4300 CPU emulators, with dynamic recompilers for 32-bit {{Keyword|x86}} and 64-bit {{Keyword|amd64}} systems, and necessary plugins for audio, graphical rendering (RDP), signal co-processor (RSP), and input. An OpenGL video plugin is included (called RiceVideo). You can use the gui (<code>gtk</code> or <code>qt4</code> USE flag) or use the command line interface (run: {{c|mupen64plus --nogui}}). View a YouTube demo [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SAq6EwHmuVE here].

