== VBA-M ==

[[File:Vbam_screenshot1.png|thumb|right|150px|VBA-M]]

VBA-M is a fork of VisualBoyAdvance and emulates Game Boy, Game Boy Color, Game Boy Advance, Super Game Boy and Super Game Boy 2. It makes an effort to bring some cohesion to the multiplicity of releases floating around the community and is actively maintained. Examples of games running on VBA-M include ''Zelda - Link's Awakening'', ''Dragon Ball Advanced'' and [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_best-selling_Game_Boy_Advance_games other highlights].


